Description:
    Install Litestack into a Rails 8.1+ application.

    Configures (core stack — no native .so required):
      - config/database.yml → adapter: litedb (preserves multi-database entries when possible)
      - config/cable.yml → adapter: litecable
      - production cache_store → :litecache (+ path under storage/)
      - config/litecache.yml → optional L1 / invalidate notes
      - production active_job.queue_adapter → :litejob
      - .gitignore → SQLite database files under db/
      - .dockerignore → same SQLite exclusions when the file exists (Rails 7.1+ default)
      - config/initializers/litestack_extensions.rb → optional libsimple / vectorlite paths
      - .gitignore → vendor/simple & vendor/vectorlite binary patterns

    Optional native extension download (needs network + python3):
      --with-simple       Download wangfenjin/simple (libsimple) into vendor/simple/
      --with-vectorlite   Download vectorlite into vendor/vectorlite/
      --with-extensions   Both of the above

    Example:
      bin/rails generate litestack:install
      bin/rails generate litestack:install --with-simple
      bin/rails generate litestack:install --with-vectorlite
      bin/rails generate litestack:install --with-extensions

    Skip download during generate (e.g. CI without network) and fetch later:
      LITESTACK_GENERATOR_SKIP_FETCH=1 bin/rails g litestack:install --with-extensions
      export LITESTACK_EXTENSION_ROOT="$PWD"
      bundle exec ruby "$(bundle show litestack)/scripts/fetch_simple.rb"

    Full guide: docs/RAILS_FULL_STACK.md

    Does NOT automatically remove solid_cache, solid_queue, their migrations, or Gemfile lines.
    Optional cleanup steps are printed after install. See docs/MIGRATING_TO_RUBY4_RAILS81.md.

    Re-running the generator is idempotent for already-configured keys.
